Max-Q enablement — required first:
•	GB300 Max-Q is not a supported SKU for dcgmi mndiag out of the box — on every compute tray, add the Max-Q device ID to the nv-hostengine environment and restart the service (the override persists at /etc/systemd/system/nvidia-dcgm.service.d/override.conf):
sudo systemctl edit nvidia-dcgm.service
  [Service]
  Environment="DCGM_MNDIAG_SUPPORTED_SKUS=31a1"
sudo systemctl restart nvidia-dcgm.service
•	Then complete the cluster prep from the References doc — OpenMPI installed on all nodes and passwordless SSH between them — and launch dcgmi mndiag. Apply the SKU override before those steps.
Example command: dcgmi mndiag --hostList "node1;node2" -p "mnubergemm.time_to_run=600"
Expected outcome: MNUBERGEMM Test | Pass with Hosts With Errors | 0 — a clean run across all detected hosts.
